-Christiansen Arms CA-10 Recon or Tactical .308

*Specs: 

Gas trap/piston operation, rotating bolt (short stroke system), reversible gas piston for suppressed or non-suppressed operation. 
Unlike some other "op-rod" systems, on the HOGAN gun, op-rod springs have been eliminated due to possible damage and system failure during sustained firing of the gun. The HOGAN gun system has been designed and manufactured to greatly decrease/eliminate heat, carbon build-up, gas leaks, fouling and wear/tear on operating parts which can have an adverse effect on an operating system. 
Each piece of operating system is hard chrome plated and/or melonite heat treated making them almost self lubricating and act as non stick surfaces making them easy to clean and maintain. 
Operates in semi-automatic, but can be made full-auto for Military and Law Enforcement. 

-UPPER RECEIVER: 
Billet machined from 7075 aluminum bar stock, (aircraft aluminum alloy), into a 
2-piece railed upper receiver to fit our Free Floating Monolithic rail system 
Electro-less *silicone Nickel on the interior (*depending on availability when rifle is shipped) 
Finished in black & NP3 

-CHARGING HANDLE: 
Billet machined from 7075 aluminum bar stock, manufactured with an oversized grip and locking latch. 
Black anodized to Mil-Spec 8625, duo colored with electro less Nickel coating/black anodize to Mil-Spec 9625 or NP3™ coated. 

-HEAT SINK BARREL NUT and WEDGEBLOCK: 
- “Patented” oversized 3.375” heat sink barrel nut design billet machined from 6061 
T-6 aluminum, heat treated and black anodized to Mil-Spec 8625 Provides strength, rigidity to rail system and works as a heat sink to greatly reduce heat buildup utilizing a larger surface area and cooling fins. Comes in sizes short, long or ribbed to meet specifications of firearm design. 
Wedgeblock comes in 2 styles fat for A3 flattop upper receiver or grooved for monolithic railed receiver, billet machined from 6061 T-6 aluminum extrusion, heat treated and black anodized to Mil-Spec 8625. 

-HANDGUARDS/RAILS: 
Aircraft aluminum alloy precision machined from 6061 T-6 extrusion Free Floating Monolithic Tactical hand guard w/ Monolithic top rail finished in black & NP3 

-PISTON and OP ROD: 
Reversible gas piston for suppressed or non-suppressed operation billet machined from 4140 high temp steel round bar, heat treated to Mil-Spec, ground to size, hard chrome plated. 
Tool steel op-rod, heat treated to Mil-Spec from PCS Company. 

-GAS BLOCK ASSEMBLY and GAS PLUG: 
Gas block: billet machined from 4140 aircraft quality steel bar stock, heat treated to Mil-Spec. 
Gas tube: 4130 aircraft quality tubing. Block and tube are joined then mated with barrel (matching serial#’s added), then melonite heat treated together. 
Gas plug: billet machined from 4140/4142 steel bar, heat treated to Mil-Spec, ground to size, mag phosphate on top, NP3 coated, and/or chrome plated with blackened top. 

-BOLT and CARRIER: 
.308 bolt: machined from 9310 steel bar stock, phosphate heat treated to Mil-Spec .308 and mag particle inspected, hard chrome plated. 
Carrier: billet machined from single piece of 8620 steel - integral keyed steel bolt carrier (machined as one piece to leave key in place). Heat treated per Mil-Spec, Nickel Teflon plated. 

-HOGAN SPECIFICATIONS: 
Smaller parts like springs, screws and washers are sourced from domestic manufacturers. 
Everything in a HOGAN gun is 100% made in the U.S.A. All raw materials are manufactured from U.S. steel mills. 
All heat treats, plating/coatings, are completed by U.S. owned and operated manufactures. 
All accessory and component parts on weapon systems are from U.S. owned and operated manufacturers. 
All HOGAN weapon systems are 100% pure American made. 

-BARREL: 
Barrel blanks are supplied by Rock Creek Barrels, Inc. and completed to final specification at Hogan Guns. 
Medium contour, hand lapped button twisted rifled, 6 fluted to improve rigidity and heat dissipation, reduce weight, improve accuracy by reducing barrel vibration when firing. 4150 Mil-B-11595 chrome moly vanadium alloy (machine gun rated). 70 Rockwell case hardened heat treated “5R” polygonal barrels are 2 times harder than Mil-Spec and hammer forged barrels. 
Corrosion resistant and 10 times thicker and harder than Mil-Spec chromed lining. The treatment on the barrels causes zero imperfections and is extremely smooth which also enables the barrels to consistently achieve excellent accuracy. 
Chamber: 7.62 x 51mm NATO (.308 Cal) “5R” polygonal right handed 1x10 twist button rifled barrels. 
Hogan X-Brake 5 prong muzzle brake and collar nut, which is remarkably effective in recoil reduction but it does not suppress the flash. Made by Hogan Guns. 

-LOWER RECEIVER: 
Billet machined from 7075-T6 aircraft aluminum alloy with integral oversized trigger guard for use with heavy gloves. 
Wire E.D.M.’d flared Magwell, ambidextrous bolt release lever machined into the lower receiver. Coated in NP3 

-PISTOL GRIP and STOCKS: 
ERGO™ pistol grip, VLTOR™ 6-position retractable buttstock with Mil-Spec tube. 
Non slip special compound rubber butt pad. Reversible for right or left handed shooters. 
Finished in black & NP3 

-TRIGGER: 
HOGAN “Gold Standard”™ trigger system, 4.5 lb. non-adjustable pull, (for zero failure) single stage competition trigger. 
Trigger, hammer & disconnector E.D.M.’d from A2 tool steel. Melonite heat treated for long life. 
Pin tubes are black oxide coated 8620 steel. Housing precision machined from 6061 billet aluminum. Deep gold anodize finish. High temp silicone cord base cushions. Complete with KNS™ precision non-rotating pins. 

-MAGAZINES: 
Although we utilize P-MAG LR-308™ magazines, HOGAN firearms will fit Bushmaster, DPMS, Fulton, JP Rifles, Knights, Remington R-25, Magpul™, original AR-10 waffle magazines and any Mil-Spec .308 magazine. 
Norgon™ “Ambi catch”™ mag release 

-WEIGHT: 9 lbs. 7 oz (Tactical X-Rail) 

-LENGTH: 39 1/4 inches (collapsed), 43 1/4 (extended) 

-NP3™ Plating: NP3™ plating: combination of a nickel alloy plating combined with Polytetrafluoethylene (Teflon). NP3™ metal finish offers many benefits. 
NP3 permits firing for longer periods of time between cleaning, dirt and powder residue have no wet or oily surface to cling to. When cleaning is required, the effort needed is minimal - usually requiring only a soft cloth. 

-HOGAN rifles come complete with 48" black plastic hard case with foam liner 

Thanks!

As the business continued to grow, it was moved in 1965 to a 2,400 sf building in the then-new Belvedere Plaza Shopping Center. Explosive growth came in the early 70's and the store was moved 3 doors down in the Belvedere Plaza to a 7,000 sf building – almost double the size of the previous location. 10 years later, Grady and Ann felt that a free-standing building would best serve our customers. Property was secured in our current location and a 9,800 sf building was constructed. The name was also changed to “Grady’s Great Outdoors” at this time.

title: For Sale:  BUFFALO-BARNES LEAD FREE 45-70 MAG. +P 350 gr. TSX-FN (2150 fps) - 20 Round Box﻿﻿
postcontent:
http://extreme-impact-ammo.com/index.php?l=product_detail&p=307

 This is a super powerful 45-70 +P (or magnum) loading. It is externally identical to SAAMI spec. 45-70 ammo, but internally it generates FAR more power and pressure. So, our 45-70 ammo will fit/chamber into any 45-70 firearm. HOWEVER, its use should be limited to firearms that are built to take the +P pressures it generates.

Its use should be limited to the following firearms: All Marlin 1895 (1895 Marlins are simply 336 actions, with a 45-70 barrel screwed on) iterations made since 1972, all Browning 1885 and 1886 copies, Rossi Rio Grande, New England Arms Handi Rifle, T/C Encore, ALL falling block actions made of modern steel such as the Ruger #1 and #3, Shiloh, Christian and Pedersoli Sharps, all Winchester 1886 iterations made since 1915 and all Siamese mauser bolt actions.

This all copper expanding 350gr. TSX-FN long-for-weight bullet will penetrate about as deep as the typical premium 400gr. + lead core partition expanding bullet, yet it gives the benefits of a lighter bullet, which means it recoils less and has flatter trajectories.

We were not able to develop velocities as fast as we’d like because the long-for-weight all copper bullet crowds the limited powder capacity of the 45-70 casing. Still, 1,900+ fps is very fast and is very powerful and for those who like the benefits of the all copper Barnes TSX-FN bullet, it is a worthwhile trade off. As an added benefit for many, this reduced velocity also means significant recoil reduction.

As always, Buffalo Bore uses real world firearms to generate our published velocities. We feel the industry wide duplicitous practice of generating advertised velocities from extra long laboratory barrels is dishonest to the customer as he/she will not be able to duplicate those velocities in the real world, where it matters.

    1,931 fps -- Marlin 1895, 22-inch barrel
    1,914 fps -- Marlin 1895, 18-inch barrel

Many shooters do not understand why the 45-70 needs very little barrel length to obtain maximum velocities. As evidenced by the above velocities, ANY straight walled (not a bottle neck case such as the 06 or any number of casings that have a shoulder) case that uses relatively fast burning rifle powders, will generate all the velocity possible in barrels much shorter than bottleneck chamberings.
